Robert Julian-Borchak Williams was wrongfully arrested because racist 
facial recognition technology misidentified him for a crime he did not

A Black man in Detroit was wrongfully arrested by police who mis-identified 
him with a false facial recognition hit. Robert Williams was held in police 
custody for a day. It's the first publicly reported case of AI resulting in 
a false arrest in the US.

Michigan police say facial recognition is just for investigative leads and 
the onus is on the investigators to make sure they're right. 
Understandable, but doesn't change the fact that the tech has been proven, 
repeatedly, to be bias against Black people:

Detroit police challenged over "unthinkingly" relying on facial recognition 
technology that mistakenly identified Black man, leading to humiliating

Robert Julian-Borchak Williams was wrongfully arrested because racist 
facial recognition technology misidentified him for a crime he did not 
commit. We can't allow this to happen again. It's time to ban facial

A Black man in Detroit was wrongfully arrested by police who mis-identified 
him with a false facial recognition hit. Robert Williams was held in police 
custody for a day. It's the first publicly reported case of AI resulting in 
a false arrest in the US.

the onus is on the investigators to make sure they're right.

repeatedly, to be bias against Black people:

Detroit police challenged over "unthinkingly" relying on facial recognition 
technology that mistakenly identified Black man, leading to humiliating 
arrest outside his home
